{
  "title": "Oversmack",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "lines": [
        "Smack with the whole",
        "Move surface as a",
        "step-FX editor.",
        "",
        "Reads Move's input",
        "(mic, line, USB-C)",
        "and keeps running",
        "while suspended.",
        "",
        "Open it from the",
        "overtake menu",
        "(Shift+Vol+Jog).",
        "Back hides the UI;",
        "audio keeps going.",
        "Shift+Vol+Jog exits."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Quick Start",
      "lines": [
        "1. Set Loop Len.",
        "2. Play something",
        " into Move's input.",
        "3. Hit Capture to",
        " grab the last",
        " loop length.",
        "4. Press a step,",
        " then tap a pad in",
        " the upper rows to",
        " set its effect.",
        "5. Re-Roll for a",
        " new random",
        " pattern; edits",
        " stay locked."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Grid",
      "lines": [
        "Steps 1-16: the",
        "slice pattern, one",
        "color per effect,",
        "white is playhead.",
        "Press to select a",
        "slice for editing",
        "(shown green).",
        "",
        "Upper 3 pad rows:",
        "effect palette,",
        "grouped by family:",
        "row 2 = stutter",
        "(reds) + tape",
        "(orange); row 3 =",
        "reverse (blue),",
        "pitch (purple),",
        "shape (grey); row 4",
        "= filter (green),",
        "space (cyan), dist",
        "(bright green).",
        "Top-right pad =",
        "Unlock.",
        "",
        "Bottom row:",
        "Capture, Arm, A/B,",
        "Re-Roll, Clear.",
        "",
        "Play button still",
        "controls Move.",
        "",
        "Loops over 16",
        "slices:",
        "use the left/right",
        "arrows or the jog",
        "wheel to move",
        "through the bars.",
        "",
        "HOLD A/B: momentary",
        "punch — flips while",
        "held, snaps back on",
        "release.",
        "",
        "With no step",
        "selected: HOLD a",
        "palette pad to punch",
        "that effect on the",
        "whole loop; pad",
        "pressure bends the",
        "effect. Release to",
        "return."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Knobs",
      "lines": [
        "1: FX Density",
        "2: Order Density",
        "3: Loop Length",
        "4: Slice Res",
        "5: Wet",
        "6: Re-Roll",
        "7: A/B",
        "8: Seed",
        "",
        "Hold Shift: knob",
        "page 2 (Pan L/R,",
        "Channels, Loop Len,",
        "BPM, Monitor); the",
        "steps show only the",
        "pinned slices.",
        "",
        "Wet = how effected",
        "the loop is: 0 =",
        "clean loop, 100 =",
        "full pattern. The",
        "loop always plays;",
        "dry input follows",
        "the Monitor pad."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Editing & Locks",
      "lines": [
        "Select a step, then",
        "TAP a palette pad:",
        "sets that effect.",
        "The next Re-Roll",
        "replaces it.",
        "",
        "HOLD a palette pad:",
        "pins the effect so",
        "Re-Roll keeps it.",
        "Pinned slices show",
        "*pin on screen and",
        "light up while",
        "Shift is held.",
        "",
        "Unlock (top-right",
        "pad) un-pins the",
        "selected slice.",
        "HOLD Re-Roll clears",
        "every pin and rolls",
        "fresh."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Dual Mono",
      "lines": [
        "Dual Mono treats L",
        "and R inputs as two",
        "mono signals, each",
        "with its own effect",
        "pattern, panned",
        "into the stereo",
        "field (Pan L/Pan R).",
        "",
        "Bottom pad row 7:",
        "toggle the mode.",
        "Pad 8: tap = edit L",
        "or R lane; hold +",
        "knob 1 or 2 = pans.",
        "",
        "A side plays the",
        "raw stereo loop;",
        "B side plays the",
        "panned lanes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Seed & Re-Roll",
      "lines": [
        "Seed browses",
        "patterns by number:",
        "the same seed always",
        "gives the same",
        "pattern.",
        "",
        "Turn slowly for one",
        "seed at a time; turn",
        "fast across 1-9999.",
        "",
        "Re-Roll varies the",
        "current seed for a",
        "fresh pattern; dial",
        "the Seed knob to",
        "return to the",
        "canonical one."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Feedback Guard",
      "lines": [
        "Speakers on with no",
        "line-in cable means",
        "the internal mic",
        "can feed back.",
        "",
        "When that risk is",
        "present the input",
        "monitoring is muted",
        "automatically: the",
        "Monitor pad turns",
        "red, capture still",
        "works, and the loop",
        "stays audible.",
        "",
        "Tap the Monitor pad",
        "to override, or",
        "plug in headphones",
        "or a line-in cable",
        "to restore it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "BPM Detect",
      "lines": [
        "Shift + Re-Roll",
        "listens to the last",
        "8 seconds of input",
        "and detects its",
        "tempo (60-180 BPM).",
        "",
        "The result becomes",
        "the free-run tempo,",
        "so Capture grabs",
        "true bars of the",
        "source. Shown as",
        "@BPM in the title.",
        "",
        "MIDI clock always",
        "wins when running.",
        "Needs material with",
        "clear hits; pads",
        "and drones report",
        "no tempo."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Sync & Transport",
      "lines": [
        "Set Move's MIDI",
        "Clock to Out so",
        "the loop locks to",
        "the transport.",
        "",
        "Without it, the",
        "loop free-runs at",
        "the project tempo.",
        "",
        "The Play button is",
        "passed through to",
        "Move, so transport",
        "and clock work",
        "under this UI."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Web Editor",
      "lines": [
        "Open the schwung",
        "manager in a browser",
        "(move.local) and go",
        "to Remote UI.",
        "",
        "oversmack: Tool tab.",
        "smack-in: its slot.",
        "",
        "Full slice grid,",
        "per-slice effect +",
        "parameter editing,",
        "effect presets, and",
        "named layouts that",
        "re-apply a whole",
        "pattern (seed +",
        "pins) to any loop.",
        "",
        "Edits sync live in",
        "both directions."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Screen Reader",
      "lines": [
        "With the screen",
        "reader on (Global",
        "Settings), steps,",
        "pads, knob changes",
        "and loop state are",
        "all announced."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
